n Snooker Championship]]}}\n| {{flagicon|WAL}} [[David John (snooker player)|David John]]\n| 3\u20137\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n| 1.\n| 2005\n| {{nowrap|[[Welsh Amateur Championship (snooker)|Welsh Amateur Championship]]}}\n| {{flagicon|WAL}} {{sortname|Michael|White|Michael White (snooker player)}}\n| 6\u20134\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Runner-up\n| 2.\n| 2007\n| [[International Open Series|PIOS \u2013 Event 2]]\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Kuldesh Johal]]\n| 4\u20136\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n| 2.\n| 2010\n| {{nowrap|[[Welsh Amateur Championship (snooker)|Welsh Amateur Championship]]}}\n| {{flagicon|WAL}} {{sortname|Gareth|Allen}}\n| 8\u20130\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Runner-up\n| 3.\n| [[2016 IBSF World Snooker Championship \u2013 Men's|2016]]\n| [[IBSF World Snooker Championship]]\n| {{flagicon|IRN}} {{sortname|Soheil|Vahedi}}\n| 1\u20138\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Runner-up\n| 4.\n| [[Challenge Tour 2019/2020|2019]]\n| [[Challenge Tour (snooker)|Challenge Tour - Event 2]]\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jake Nicholson (snooker player)|Jake Nicholson]]\n| 1\u20133\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98FB98\"|Winner\n| 3.\n| [[2019/20 Challenge Tour 3|2019]]\n| [[Challenge Tour (snooker)|Challenge Tour - Event 3]]\n| {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Robbie McGuigan]]\n| 3\u20131\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Runner-up\n| 5.\n| [[Challenge Tour 2019/2020|2019]]\n| [[Challenge Tour (snooker)|Challenge Tour - Event 7]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Dean Young (snooker player)|Dean Young]]\n| 1\u20133\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Winner\n| 4.\n| 2020\n| [[EBSA European Snooker Championship]]\n| {{flagicon|FIN}} [[Heikki Niva]]\n| 5\u20132\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*\n*[http://www.worldsnooker.com/players/andrew-pagett/ Andrew Pagett] at ''worldsnooker.com''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100806161021/http://www.global-snooker.com/Andrew-Pagett.asp Profile on Global Snooker]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pagett, Andrew}}\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Newport, Wales]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Welsh snooker players]]\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox snooker player\n|name         = Andrew Pagett\n|image        = Andrew Pagett PHC 2011-1.jpg\n|caption      =  Paul Hunter Classic 2011\n|birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1982|4|25}}\n|birth_place   = [[Newport, Wales|Newport]], [[Wales]]\n| Sport country = {{WAL}}\n| Nickname     = The Welsh Wizard<ref name=\"Big Interview\">{{cite news| url = http://snookerscene.blogspot.com/2011/04/big-interview-andrew-pagett.html | title = The Big Interview: Andrew Pagett | website = Snooker Scene | date = 12 April 2011 | accessdate = 12 April 2011 | location=}}</ref>\n| Professional = 2008/2009, 2010\u20132012, 2013\u20132015, 2020\u2013\n| High ranking = 70 <small>(June\u2013July 2011, October 2011)</small><ref>{{cite web|title=Rankings after PTC1 2011 |url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/80/80/0,,13165~163968,00.pdf |website=worldsnooker.com |publisher=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]] |format=PDF |accessdate=1 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928215440/http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/80/80/0%2C%2C13165~163968%2C00.pdf |archivedate=28 September 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Issued after the Players Tour Championship 2011 \u2013 Event 7 |url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/6b/90/0,,13165~168043,00.pdf |date=11 October 2011 |work=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association|World Snooker]] |format=PDF |accessdate=31 December 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213034305/http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/6b/90/0%2C%2C13165~168043%2C00.pdf |archivedate=13 December 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n| Prize money  = \u00a351,765\n| High break   = '''112''': <br> <small>2010 MIUS Cup</small>\n| Century break = 7\n| Best finish  = Last 32 <small>([[2011 World Snooker Championship|2011 World Championship]], [[2014 Welsh Open (snooker)|2014 Welsh Open]], [[2015 Indian Open]])</small>\n| Ranking wins = \n| Other wins   = \n| World champ  = \n}}\n\n'''Andrew Pagett''' (born 25 April 1982) is a Welsh professional [[snooker|snooker player]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Early career===\n\nHe played on [[Challenge Tour (snooker)|Challenge Tour]] from 2003 to 2005, and first qualified for the Main Tour in [[Snooker season 2008/2009|2008/2009]], but lost his place after just one season. He regained his place for the [[Snooker season 2010/2011|2010/2011]] season by topping the Welsh rankings. He is a practice partner of [[Mark Williams (snooker player)|Mark Williams]].\n\n===2010/2011 season===\n\nPagett qualified for the [[2011 World Snooker Championship]] after winning four qualifying matches. He knocked out [[Zhang Anda]], [[Bjorn Haneveer]] and [[Nigel Bond]], before beating [[Andrew Higginson]] 10\u20136 to qualify for the final stages of a major event for the first time,<ref name=\"Pagett thanks Mark Williams after qualifying success\">{{cite news| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/other_sports/snooker/9424713.stm | title = Pagett thanks Mark Williams after qualifying success | work = [[BBC Sport]] | date = 14 March 2011 | accessdate = 27 March 2011 | location=}}</ref> where he was defeated 10\u20137 by [[Jamie Cope]].\n\n===2011/2012 season===\n\nPagett began the [[Snooker season 2011/2012|2011/2012 season]] ranked 71st in the world meaning he would have to win four qualifying matches to reach the ranking event main draws.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rankings after 2011 World Championship |url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/64/71/0,,13165~160100,00.pdf |website=worldsnooker.com |publisher=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association]] |format=PDF |accessdate=23 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/66Gdb52fS?url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/64/71/0%2C%2C13165~160100%2C00.pdf |archivedate=19 March 2012 }}</ref> However, after attempting to qualify for all eight tournaments he only won two matches; one at the [[2011 Australian Goldfields Open|Australian Goldfields Open]] and the other at the [[2012 German Masters|German Masters]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://snooker.org/res/index.asp?player=65&season=2011 | title=Andrew Pagett 2011/2012 | website=snooker.org | accessdate=23 May 2012}}</ref> Pagett played in 11 of the 12 minor-ranking [[Players Tour Championship 2011/2012|Players Tour Championship]] events throughout the season, with his best finishes coming in [[Players Tour Championship 2011/2012 \u2013 Event 4|Event 4]] and [[Players Tour Championship 2011/2012 \u2013 Event 9|Event 9]], where he reached the last 32. He was ranked number 82 on the PTC [[Players Tour Championship 2011/2012#Order of Merit|Order of Merit]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snooker.org/res/index.asp?template=10&season=2011|title=Order of Merit|website=snooker.org|date=8 January 2012|accessdate=11 April 2012}}</ref> Pagett finished the season without a world ranking and will not play on the main tour in the [[Snooker season 2012/2013|2012/2013 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/1d/b0/0,,13165~176157,00.pdf |title=Official World Snooker Ranking List for the 2012/2013 Season |date=8 May 2012 |accessdate=23 May 2012 |work=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association|World Snooker]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69tDLWozD?url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/1d/b0/0%2C%2C13165~176157%2C00.pdf |archivedate=13 August 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n===2012/2013 season===\n\nPagett could only enter Players Tour Championship events in the 2012/2013 season, taking part in seven of them. His best finish came in the [[European Tour 2012/2013 \u2013 Event 3|third European Tour event]] in Belgium, where he beat Raf van de Maele, [[Robbie Williams (snooker player)|Robbie Williams]], [[Stuart Bingham]], [[Thepchaiya Un-Nooh]] and former world champion [[Neil Robertson (snooker player)|Neil Robertson]], before losing to [[Mark Allen (snooker player)|Mark Allen]] 1\u20134 in the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://snooker.org/res/index.asp?player=65&season=2012 | title=Andrew Pagett 2012/2013 | website=snooker.org | accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref> It was this result which largely contributed to him finishing 55th on the Order of Merit to claim one of the eight spots on offer to players not on the main tour for the [[Snooker season 2013/2014|2013/2014]] and [[Snooker season 2014/2015|2014/2015]] seasons.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.snooker.org/res/index.asp?template=10 | title=Order of Merit 2012/2013 | website=snooker.org | accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n===2013/2014 season===\nPagett made a dream start to the season as in his first match he defeated world number one [[Mark Selby]] 5\u20133 to qualify for the [[2013 Wuxi Classic]] in China where he lost 2\u20135 to [[David Gilbert (snooker player)|David Gilbert]] in the first round.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/snooker/22682698 | title=Mark Selby suffers Wuxi Classic defeat by Andrew Pagett | date=27 May 2013 | work=[[BBC Sport]] | accessdate=30 May 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"2013/14\">{{cite web|title=Andrew Pagett 2013/2014|url=http://www.snooker.org/res/index.asp?player=65&season=2013|website=snooker.org|accessdate=17 June 2013}}</ref> Later in the year he reached the last 32 of a ranking event for only the second time in his career at his home tournament the [[2014 Welsh Open (snooker)|Welsh Open]]. Pagett beat [[Marcus Campbell]] 4\u20130 and [[Gerard Greene]] 4\u20133, before losing 0\u20134 to [[Stephen Maguire]].<ref name=\"2013/14\"/> Pagett ended his first season back on the tour ranked world number 103.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/71/c1/0,,13165~180593,00.pdf |title=Prize Money Rankings After the World Championship 2014 |work=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association|World Snooker]] |accessdate=8 May 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508030740/http://www.worldsnooker.com/staticFiles/71/c1/0%2C%2C13165~180593%2C00.pdf |archivedate=8 May 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n===2014/2015 season===\nAfter losing in the qualifying rounds of the first three events of the [[Snooker season 2014/2015|2014/2015 season]], Pagett beat [[Rory McLeod (snooker player)|Rory McLeod]] 6\u20133 to play in the [[2014 International Championship|International Championship]], where he lost 1\u20136 to [[Peter Ebdon]]. He was knocked out of the first round of both the [[2014 UK Championship (snooker)|UK Championship]] and [[2015 Welsh Open (snooker)|Welsh Open]] 6\u20132 by [[Mike Dunn (snooker player)|Mike Dunn]] and 4\u20132 by McLeod respectively. Pagett's only win at the venue of a ranking this year was a 4\u20132 success over Zack Richardson at the [[2015 Indian Open|Indian Open]], before he lost 1\u20134 to [[Chris Wakelin]] in the second round.<ref name=\"2014/15\">{{cite web|title=Andrew Pagett 2014/2015|url=http://www.snooker.org/res/index.asp?season=2014&player=65|website=snooker.org|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref> He was relegated from the tour at the end of the season as the number 80 in the world rankings and did not enter [[World Snooker Tour#Q School|Q School]].<ref>{{cite web|title=World Rankings After 2015 Betfred World Championship|url=http://www.worldsnooker.com/rankings/|work=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association|World Snooker]]|accessdate=8 May 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150507001308/http://www.worldsnooker.com/rankings/|archivedate=7 May 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Performance and rankings timeline==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! '''Tournament'''\n! [[Snooker season 2003/2004|2003/<br/>04]]\n! [[Snooker season 2004/2005|2004/<br/>05]]\